<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Playbook · 2026</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">How to Write Linkedin Articles with Claude: <em>step-by-step.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Practical playbook for drafting LinkedIn long-form that builds personal brand. Used regularly by executives and thought leaders.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Use Claude to write LinkedIn articles via a structured prompt + your specific context. The key: collaborate with Claude rather than asking it to do it for you. 3-5× faster output with your judgment intact.</p></div>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">The workflow</h2>
<ol class="ol">
<li><strong>Set up a Claude Project</strong> with relevant context (audience, brand voice, examples).</li>
<li><strong>Write a structured prompt</strong> (specific audience, format, length, constraints — not 'help me write LinkedIn articles').</li>
<li><strong>Iterate on the first draft.</strong> Each round improves the output.</li>
<li><strong>Edit for voice and accuracy.</strong> Claude gets you 80%; you finish the last 20%.</li>
<li><strong>Save the working prompt</strong> for next time.</li>
</ol>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What to avoid</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Vague prompts — specifics in produces specifics out</li>
<li>Publishing without editing</li>
<li>Skipping the Project setup (you'll repeat context every time)</li>
<li>Treating Claude as a writer rather than a thinking partner</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><div class="cta-box">
<div><div class="cta-text">Want help operationalizing this across your team?</div><div class="cta-sub">The $1,500 AI Audit includes role-specific Claude workflows.</div></div>
<a href="/services/ai-audit" class="btn-p">Book →</a>
</div></div></section>

